Anel Elektrik, Erdemir, Koc: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-17T07:27:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/anel-elektrik-erdemir-koc-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 933.51, or
1.5 percent, to 63,280.42 yesterday.  Anel Elektrik Proje Taahhut & Ticaret AS (ANELE TI): The
Turkish contractor of electromechanical services said it got an
additional contract valued at 151.2 million Qatari rials ($41.5
million) from Sky Oryx JV for the New Doha Airport, according to
a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the market
closed yesterday. The company plans to complete the work by
October, it said. Anel Elektrik dropped 2 kurus, or 0.9 percent,
to 2.14 liras.  Eregli Demir & Celik Fabrikalari TAS (EREGL TI): Turkey’s
biggest flat steelmaker was raised to “neutral” from “sell”
at Goldman Sachs Group Inc., according to a report today.
Erdemir declined 2 kurus, or 0.5 percent, to 3.92 liras.    Koc Holding AS (KCHOL)  : Turkey’s biggest group of
companies plans to distribute 550 million liras ($345.6 million)
of dividends from 2010 profit on April 14. The holding will
propose a gross dividend payment of 0.22773 lira per share to a  shareholders’ meeting  on April 7, it said in a statement to the
bourse after the market closed yesterday. Koc Holding fell 26
kurus, or 3.6 percent, to 6.98 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
